'''Rupnagar''' is a town in [[Punjab]], [[India]]. It was formerly known as '''Ropar'''. The town of Rupnagar is said to have been founded by a Raja called Rokeshar, who ruled during the 11th century and named it after his son Rup Sen. It is also the site of an ancient town of the [[Indus Valley Civilization]].
